The paper is about a language model for scientific text, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised pretraining and achieving state-of-the-art results, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common topic in neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
